 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=406%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=814%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1222%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1630%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Side view of glasses showing two-part lens\" title=\"HindSight Edge Sport\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> HindSight’s glasses rely on a unique two-part lens design.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>HindSight</i></span></p></div><p>It also offers a potential aerodynamic bonus because it reduces the need to change position on the bike – a real concern for time triallists, in particular.</p><p>The HindSight Edge glasses rely on two-part angled lenses with sections of semi-transparent mirror at the outer edges, to offer a view behind.</p><p>The brand says it studied the optics of the eye as well as cyclists’ real-world experiences to arrive at a final design.</p><p>It’s fair to say, conventional bike mirrors aren’t beloved of performance-oriented cyclists, however practical they may or may not be. Could you be tempted by a stealthier glasses-based alternative? Let us know your thoughts in the comments below.</p></section></div>","author":"Matthew Loveridge","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"067dd950e0182e206e46f803e74c6ce474f82f4d089a04975ed03651a276825b","category":"Cycling"}